traditionally chart of accounts are the collection of all accounts that are used to store transactions.

Eg: current assets, current liabilites and equity. also the accounts that are inside the granularity of these.

in epbcs, account dimension is core of chart of accounts, along with other dimensions

traditional chart of accounts are stored under account dimension

COA in ERP and EPM systems:
Account (represent actual transaction stored)
Entity ( representing the organizational structure granularity of how business is operating)
flow of budget is modelled using entity
Scenario ( represents what it is qualified for, whether it is meant for plan, or budget and for comparision )
version ( represents state of data, whether it is final, or draft or working)
period ( represents the data value for particular period)
year ( represents data associated with particular year)
currency ( for multi currency applications, represents the transactional currency or planned currency)
custom dimensions ( product, department, market)( for qualifying and planning data based on cust dimns)


